by Wexas » Sat Aug 15, 2020 7:25 pm

One of the seven nations after Japan collapsed is the Republic of Ezo. The Republic, based on the 1869 Republic of the same name, is a self-proclaimed Democratic Socialist nation with full suffrage for all citizens and regard for human rights. The economy itself follows a Market Socialist model, with companies being run by the workers but still competing with one another. Due to this factor and a few others, Ezo is a major nation in the field of Electronics with companies that were massive in the OTL like Sony being based there

Unfortunately for this bright little sliver of Japanese Hope, it appears to be the smallest of the seven states that we know of so far. So I find it unlikely that, without support from the USSR, their ideas will get very far. (Of course, this ain't my nation, so what do I know?)

by Wuchu » Sat Aug 15, 2020 7:32 pm

In their universe, the Americas became balkanised and grew to be ruled by warlords - similar to the Warring States period of China - and feudal ideas became mainstream as society regressed back towards Medieval ideas. Through this struggle and isolation, a duchy had managed to develop its own culture based around the Texan wetlands. The duchy eventually became a kingdom, as dynasties came and went.

I like this. It seems very much like you've taken the history of imperial China and have applied it to a more recent empire. It's a good exercise in predictive historism.

AN: it's the story of an opportunist authoritarian man who wanted power. It's actually quite interesting to read about, despite it being a total shitpost of a nation.
